metadata.description:
A collection of images about mail and how they serve the communities around us and their untold stories.

This specific USPS is located in San Rafael, CA. It is a very cool looking building inspired by The Marin County Civic Center, designed by Frank Lloyd Wright (which is located directly behind it). Which was featured in the film Gattaca.


Plus Code: XFXC+2H San Rafael, California
